WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:48.641 --> 01:53.512
RARBG.COM Max: They say there's power
in Boston.

01:53.514 --> 01:58.550
Some phone service in Denver.

01:58.552 --> 02:02.888
But things are far
from what they were.

02:06.459 --> 02:10.496
Maybe it was all inevitable.

02:10.497 --> 02:15.267
An unavoidable collision between
mankind and technology.

02:22.609 --> 02:27.246
The Internet was meant to make
the world a smaller place.

02:29.382 --> 02:33.285
But it actually feels smaller
without it.

02:42.428 --> 02:46.865
I knew will and Evelyn caster
better than anyone.

02:48.434 --> 02:52.738
I knew their brilliance.

02:52.740 --> 02:55.874
Their dedication
to what they believed in.

02:57.777 --> 03:00.312
And to what they loved.

03:00.314 --> 03:03.382
[ <i> Jorma kaukonen's "genesis"</i>
<i> plays</i> ]

03:12.525 --> 03:17.095
¶<i> The time has come</i>
<i> for us to pause</i> ¶

03:18.631 --> 03:21.300
¶<i> and think of living</i>
<i> as it was</i> ¶

03:21.302 --> 03:23.902
[ device clicks, will grunts ]

03:23.904 --> 03:28.106
¶<i> Into the future</i>
<i> we must cross</i> ¶

03:28.108 --> 03:29.508
¶<i> must cross</i> ¶

03:29.510 --> 03:31.109
¶<i> I'd like to go with you</i> ¶

03:31.111 --> 03:33.879
I'm not sure
what the point is.

03:36.449 --> 03:39.551
Copper shields the
electromagnetic radiation.

03:39.553 --> 03:41.253
Yeah, I know how it works.

03:41.255 --> 03:42.721
I'm asking...

03:42.723 --> 03:44.456
"Why?"

03:44.458 --> 03:46.024
Sanctuary.

03:46.026 --> 03:50.896
Nothing gets through.
No signals of any kind.

03:50.898 --> 03:54.066
You see? Dead zone.
Nothing.

03:54.068 --> 03:56.735
Uh-huh, sure, but you could
just turn it off.

03:56.737 --> 04:00.772
Yeah, but fewer distractions
is what you wanted, right?

04:00.774 --> 04:02.207
Isn't it?
[ Laughs ]

04:02.209 --> 04:05.644
Yeah.
That's what I wanted.

04:05.646 --> 04:06.745
Come on, we'll be late.

04:06.747 --> 04:08.213
For what?

04:20.660 --> 04:22.361
Hey, you know what?

04:22.363 --> 04:23.729
What?

04:23.731 --> 04:26.898
I really think I'm starting
to make progress on this.

04:26.900 --> 04:28.634
Hey!

04:28.636 --> 04:30.502
You need to get dressed.

04:34.907 --> 04:36.541
[ Sighs ]

04:36.543 --> 04:40.078
I don't know why you bother
with these proofs.

04:40.080 --> 04:41.880
Yeah, only three people
in the world even care.

04:41.882 --> 04:43.115
Because it's fun.

04:43.117 --> 04:45.284
You sure you're up
for this?

04:45.286 --> 04:48.620
No. Not remotely.
Really?

04:48.622 --> 04:50.088
Will, it's important.

04:50.090 --> 04:52.591
I know,
but your donors are fools.

04:52.593 --> 04:54.526
They just sit there
in a daze

04:54.528 --> 04:57.062
waiting for me to say the words
"commercial application."

04:57.064 --> 04:58.096
It kills me.

04:58.098 --> 05:00.432
Well,
the "fools" there today

05:00.434 --> 05:03.268
could fund us
for the next 5 years.

05:03.270 --> 05:04.603
Well, then I suppose
in that case

05:04.605 --> 05:06.238
I have every reason
to behave.

05:06.240 --> 05:07.339
Yes.

05:07.341 --> 05:08.707
But if this goes well,

05:08.709 --> 05:10.208
please, you have to
promise me that I'll,

05:10.210 --> 05:11.543
I'll never have to do this
ever again.

05:11.545 --> 05:12.644
Never. Promise.

05:12.646 --> 05:13.712
Okay. I promise.

05:13.714 --> 05:14.913
Really?
Sure.

05:14.915 --> 05:15.947
I promise.

05:15.949 --> 05:17.949
[ Laughs ]

05:17.951 --> 05:20.352
You're lying.

05:23.189 --> 05:25.524
[ Radio chatter ]

05:29.996 --> 05:31.430
[ Bell jingles ]

05:48.147 --> 05:50.582
[ Indistinct conversation ]

05:52.985 --> 05:57.889
All: Happy Birthday,
dear Aaron!

05:57.891 --> 06:01.193
Happy Birthday to you!

06:01.195 --> 06:04.329
[ Applause ]

06:18.077 --> 06:20.345
Man: Jason,
other side of the stage.

06:20.347 --> 06:21.813
Yeah, I'd like to do
a camera check

06:21.815 --> 06:23.115
and a sound check together.

06:23.117 --> 06:24.383
You'll do the first block,

06:24.385 --> 06:26.284
followed by mcrae,
llewellyn, and --

06:26.286 --> 06:27.452
ah, then the main event.

06:27.454 --> 06:29.855
Evelyn: Max.
Ev, how are you?

06:29.857 --> 06:31.423
Good.

06:31.425 --> 06:33.158
Ready to sing
for your supper?

06:33.160 --> 06:34.793
I'm sorry to put you
through it.

06:34.795 --> 06:37.229
Doctor caster?
Sorry. Would you mind?

06:37.231 --> 06:38.597
Sure thing.

06:38.599 --> 06:40.565
Thanks.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.134
What?

06:42.136 --> 06:44.836
You have groupies?
Why don't I get groupies?

06:44.838 --> 06:46.772
Excuse me. Doctor waters, would
you like to do a run through?

06:46.774 --> 06:48.740
Yes, please.
I'll see you backstage.
Alright.

06:56.649 --> 06:58.283
[ Door unlocks ]

06:58.285 --> 07:00.385
Doctor Casey:
<i> Important distinction, um...</i>

07:00.387 --> 07:05.590
<i> This created brain</i>
<i> is self-sustaining.</i>

07:05.592 --> 07:09.594
<i> And it's capable of, er,</i>
<i> of emotional expressivity.</i>

07:09.596 --> 07:12.898
<i> And, um, of self-awareness.</i>

07:14.967 --> 07:18.236
The effort to develop a strong
artificial intelligence

07:18.238 --> 07:20.372
has led to significant
advancements

07:20.374 --> 07:22.507
in the field
of neural engineering,

07:22.509 --> 07:24.709
as well as our understanding
of the human brain.

07:24.711 --> 07:28.947
But while some focus
on the still-distant dream

07:28.949 --> 07:30.549
of a thinking computer,

07:30.551 --> 07:34.453
I believe the journey
to be more important

07:34.455 --> 07:36.455
than the destination.

07:36.457 --> 07:39.057
My priority is to use

07:39.059 --> 07:41.126
my colleagues'
accidental insights

07:41.128 --> 07:43.829
to develop new methods for
the early detection of cancer.

07:43.831 --> 07:47.165
And in the hopes of finding
a cure for Alzheimer's.

07:47.167 --> 07:49.601
Simply put, to save lives.

07:49.603 --> 07:52.838
[ Applause ]

08:08.621 --> 08:11.923
Evelyn: "A new type of thinking
is essential,

08:11.925 --> 08:15.727
if mankind is to survive
and move toward higher levels."

08:15.729 --> 08:19.498
Albert Einstein said that
more than 50 years ago.

08:19.500 --> 08:23.301
And it couldn't be more relevant
than it is today.

08:23.303 --> 08:25.937
Intelligent machines
will soon allow us

08:25.939 --> 08:28.974
to conquer our most
intractable challenges.

08:28.976 --> 08:33.111
Not merely to cure disease,
but to end poverty and hunger.

08:33.113 --> 08:34.880
To heal the planet.

08:34.881 --> 08:37.582
And build a better future
for all of us.

08:37.583 --> 08:39.985
I don't know anybody
who is doing more

08:39.986 --> 08:43.388
to make that future a reality
than our next speaker.

08:43.390 --> 08:45.924
But then again,
I'm probably biased.

08:45.926 --> 08:47.459
[ Laughter ]

08:47.461 --> 08:50.395
Please welcome my partner
in science and in life.

08:50.397 --> 08:53.999
Doctor will caster.

08:54.001 --> 08:55.367
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:00.206 --> 09:01.873
Will:
Thank you very much.

09:01.875 --> 09:04.943
My wife has always been eager
to change the world.

09:04.945 --> 09:08.446
But I'll just settle
for understanding it first.

09:08.448 --> 09:10.081
[ Light laughter ]

09:10.083 --> 09:13.952
For one hundred
and thirty thousand years,

09:13.954 --> 09:18.123
our capacity for reason
has remained unchanged.

09:18.125 --> 09:22.294
The combined intellect
of the neuroscientists,

09:22.296 --> 09:25.931
engineers, mathematicians
and hackers...

09:25.933 --> 09:27.432
[ Laughter ]

09:27.434 --> 09:29.534
...in this auditorium

09:29.536 --> 09:34.172
pales in comparison
to even the most basic a.I.

09:34.174 --> 09:36.374
Once online a sentient machine

09:36.376 --> 09:39.911
will quickly overcome the limits
of biology.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.413
And in a short time,

09:41.415 --> 09:44.316
its analytical power
will be greater

09:44.318 --> 09:47.118
than the collective intelligence

09:47.120 --> 09:52.123
of every person born
in the history of the world.

09:52.125 --> 09:54.593
[ Phone ringing ]

10:04.403 --> 10:06.571
So now imagine such an entity

10:06.573 --> 10:09.474
with a full range
of human emotion.

10:09.476 --> 10:11.009
Even self-awareness.

10:11.011 --> 10:17.015
Some scientists refer to this
as "the singularity."

10:17.017 --> 10:19.818
I call it "transcendence."

10:19.820 --> 10:25.790
The path to building
such a super-intelligence

10:25.792 --> 10:29.060
requires us to unlock
the most fundamental secrets

10:29.062 --> 10:30.662
of the universe.

10:30.664 --> 10:33.798
What is the nature
of consciousness?

10:33.800 --> 10:36.968
[ Flatline ]

10:38.871 --> 10:40.505
Is there a soul?

10:42.141 --> 10:43.274
[ Monkey screeches ]

10:43.276 --> 10:46.945
And if so, where does it reside?

10:53.352 --> 10:55.153
Man: Doctor caster?

10:55.155 --> 10:58.890
Yes, sir?
You have a question?

11:02.461 --> 11:06.931
So you wanna create a God?

11:06.933 --> 11:08.500
Your own God?

11:08.502 --> 11:11.636
That's a very good question.

11:11.638 --> 11:17.676
Um, isn't that what man
has always done?

11:20.179 --> 11:21.780
Doctor?

11:21.782 --> 11:23.248
Max:
Oh, it's relentless!

11:23.250 --> 11:24.783
Thank you.

11:24.785 --> 11:26.484
Look, and now he's, now he's
pretending he's not enjoying it.

11:26.486 --> 11:27.886
Yabber yabber yabber.

11:27.888 --> 11:29.254
Doctor caster.
Pleasure.

11:29.256 --> 11:32.090
Thank you.

11:32.092 --> 11:34.292
Professor?

11:34.294 --> 11:37.429
[ Gunshot, all screaming ]

11:37.431 --> 11:39.130
You're all slaves!

11:39.132 --> 11:42.600
[ Gunshot ]

11:42.602 --> 11:46.438
Woman: <i> Hours ago,</i>
<i> this facility was attacked.</i>

11:46.440 --> 11:49.474
<i> We can now confirm at least</i>
<i> five people are dead.</i>

11:49.476 --> 11:51.476
<i> Twelve people</i>
<i> have been injured.</i>

11:51.478 --> 11:52.811
<i> This incident is related</i>

11:52.813 --> 11:54.913
<i> to a series</i>
<i> of simultaneous attacks</i>

11:54.915 --> 11:57.182
<i> that took place today</i>
<i> in New York City,</i>

11:57.184 --> 12:00.385
<i> Los Angeles, Chicago</i>
<i> and Washington, D.C.,</i>

12:00.387 --> 12:04.055
<i> all of them targeting major</i>
<i> computer and research labs</i>

12:04.057 --> 12:06.057
<i> in the field of advanced</i>
<i> artificial intelligence.</i>

12:06.059 --> 12:07.826
<i> So far no one has claimed</i>
<i> responsibility.</i>

12:07.828 --> 12:10.862
Max: No, he's alright.
He was very lucky.

12:10.864 --> 12:14.265
The bullet only grazed him.
Yup. Okay. Take care.

12:14.267 --> 12:17.502
They hit a.I. Labs
all over the country.

12:17.504 --> 12:19.471
Tom Casey's dead.

12:19.473 --> 12:23.141
And they took out Joseph's
entire team at livermore.

12:23.143 --> 12:25.343
What about Joseph?

12:25.345 --> 12:26.745
He's alright.

12:26.747 --> 12:29.514
Actually, he's at your office
with the FBI.

12:31.383 --> 12:34.018
[ Police radio chatter ]

12:41.594 --> 12:43.928
Joseph.

12:49.735 --> 12:52.403
Max.

12:52.405 --> 12:53.404
My God, will.

12:53.406 --> 12:54.773
You forgot to teach us

12:54.775 --> 12:57.075
how to dodge a bullet,
didn't you?

12:57.077 --> 12:59.711
How did they even get inside
your lab?

12:59.713 --> 13:01.112
One of my programmers.

13:01.114 --> 13:03.615
All that security
and he waltzes in

13:03.617 --> 13:04.749
with a poisoned cake.

13:04.751 --> 13:06.084
Dioxin, we think.

13:06.086 --> 13:09.521
Oh. This is agent Buchanan
with the FBI.

13:09.523 --> 13:11.489
Hey.
How do you do?

13:11.491 --> 13:12.924
Hi. [ Sighs ]

13:12.926 --> 13:14.392
I've been following your
research, doctor caster.

13:14.394 --> 13:15.593
It's fascinating.

13:15.595 --> 13:17.061
Agent Buchanan
is a close partner

13:17.063 --> 13:18.863
in my cyber-defense work
at livermore.

13:18.865 --> 13:22.534
Um, is there somewhere
where we can all talk?

13:22.536 --> 13:25.470
Could go to my office.
Just down here.

13:25.472 --> 13:27.038
Great.

13:27.040 --> 13:28.940
Buchanan: Revolutionary
independence from technology.

13:28.942 --> 13:30.275
Rift.

13:30.277 --> 13:32.410
So, till two years ago, it was
all about the disconnect.

13:32.412 --> 13:34.913
People texting instead of
actually talking to each other.

13:34.915 --> 13:37.115
Social media
as an invasion of privacy.

13:37.117 --> 13:40.151
They made a big deal of putting
smartphones in blenders.

13:40.153 --> 13:42.754
But I'm afraid we all missed
the real threat.

13:42.756 --> 13:48.293
Yeah. This guy, Joel Edmund,
was with me for a year.

13:48.295 --> 13:51.629
The guy who shot will was
working on campus since August.

13:51.631 --> 13:53.965
They infiltrated
their targets

13:53.967 --> 13:56.768
and then coordinated
their attacks.

13:56.770 --> 13:58.937
That's insane.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.438
Buchanan: An hour ago,

14:00.440 --> 14:03.007
they claimed the murders
and released their manifesto.

14:03.009 --> 14:05.844
"Artificial intelligence
is an unnatural abomination

14:05.846 --> 14:07.178
and a threat to humanity."

14:07.180 --> 14:10.381
They're determined to stop
any attempt

14:10.383 --> 14:12.917
at what you call
"transcendence."

14:12.919 --> 14:14.853
Max:
So this isn't over?

14:14.855 --> 14:17.055
Actually,
that's why I'm here.

14:17.057 --> 14:20.625
We lost decades of research
and development today.

14:20.627 --> 14:22.060
For right now, will,

14:22.062 --> 14:25.763
your lab is the only one
that can wake up a strong a.I.

14:25.765 --> 14:28.733
So the defense department
is asking --

14:28.735 --> 14:30.568
no, no, no, no. Hang on, wait.
No, there's, no.

14:30.570 --> 14:32.804
I'm not letting
the government in.

14:32.806 --> 14:35.874
We've never taken their money.
No.
No, will.

14:35.876 --> 14:38.610
They just want to know
if the work is on track.

14:38.612 --> 14:41.246
It's important
to all of us.

14:41.248 --> 14:44.215
Buchanan: We've heard a lot
about the pinn project,

14:44.217 --> 14:45.483
doctor caster.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.952
Is there, is there any way
we could have a look?

14:47.954 --> 14:50.855
Do I have a choice?

14:50.857 --> 14:54.158
Yes, of course, you do.

14:54.160 --> 14:57.729
So these are state-of-the-art
quantum processors.

14:57.731 --> 14:59.697
You won't find
faster computational power

14:59.699 --> 15:02.867
anywhere else
in the world.

15:02.869 --> 15:06.170
Pinn: <i> Good evening,</i>
<i> doctor tagger.</i>

15:07.606 --> 15:09.774
It's seen old
faculty pictures of you.

15:09.776 --> 15:14.012
<i> Good evening, Donald Buchanan.</i>

15:14.014 --> 15:15.246
It knows me?

15:15.248 --> 15:16.948
Of course it does.

15:16.950 --> 15:18.716
Dmv records.
Social media.

15:18.718 --> 15:23.888
Pinn, tell agent Buchanan
about yourself.

15:23.890 --> 15:25.256
<i> I am pinn,</i>

15:25.258 --> 15:28.793
<i> a physically independent</i>
<i> neural network</i>

15:28.795 --> 15:31.562
<i>invented by doctor will caster.</i>

15:31.564 --> 15:35.533
Can you prove
that you are self-aware?

15:35.535 --> 15:38.069
<i> That's a difficult question,</i>
<i> Dr. tagger.</i>

15:38.071 --> 15:40.972
<i> Can you prove that</i> you <i> are?</i>

15:40.974 --> 15:43.441
You can't program a machine
to be self-aware,

15:43.443 --> 15:46.744
because we have no idea how
our own consciousness works.

15:46.746 --> 15:47.946
That is your opinion.

15:47.948 --> 15:49.547
You just happen
to be wrong.

15:49.549 --> 15:52.183
Evidently, Casey managed
to solve that dilemma.

15:52.185 --> 15:56.387
He sent us his research
just before he was killed.

15:56.389 --> 15:58.389
Soon as it's packed up,
we'll send it over.

15:58.391 --> 16:00.625
I think you'll find
we'll be helpful partners,

16:00.627 --> 16:01.459
doctor caster.

16:01.461 --> 16:03.194
You alright, will?

16:03.196 --> 16:05.229
No, he needs rest.
I think we're done here.

16:05.231 --> 16:07.799
[ Mumbles ]
I'm so sorry.

16:07.801 --> 16:08.933
That's fine.

16:08.935 --> 16:10.368
Okay.
Sorry.

16:19.211 --> 16:22.413
[ Will coughing ]

16:31.991 --> 16:35.426
Will, hey, hey!

16:35.428 --> 16:37.662
Come on, sit up.

16:37.664 --> 16:39.864
Sit up, be careful.

16:39.866 --> 16:41.866
[ Panting ]

16:44.036 --> 16:47.238
Doctor Strauss: Our first
thought is always infection.

16:47.240 --> 16:50.541
But given the circumstances,
we'll widen the search.

16:50.543 --> 16:52.310
We'll figure this out.

17:12.631 --> 17:14.232
[ Device beeping ]

17:25.377 --> 17:27.211
[ Sighs ]

17:27.213 --> 17:29.080
It's an isotope
called polonium.

17:29.082 --> 17:31.215
The bullet must have been
laced with it.

17:31.217 --> 17:33.584
There were traces of it
at the wound.

17:38.057 --> 17:40.525
Well, what's the treatment?

17:40.527 --> 17:42.193
It's radiation poisoning.

17:42.195 --> 17:45.763
I'm afraid that once it enters
the bloodstream,

17:45.765 --> 17:47.732
the effect is irreversible.

17:47.734 --> 17:49.033
With proper care,

17:49.035 --> 17:51.769
we're looking at 4,
maybe 5 weeks

17:51.771 --> 17:54.372
before his system
shuts down.

18:05.250 --> 18:06.551
[ Sniffles ]

18:12.057 --> 18:14.092
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm right here.

18:21.433 --> 18:24.001
Will:
It just doesn't make sense.

18:24.003 --> 18:26.003
They're afraid of technology

18:26.005 --> 18:28.506
because of its threat
to humanity.

18:28.508 --> 18:33.010
Yet they don't flinch
at taking a life.

18:33.012 --> 18:37.949
So obviously
they're not big on logic.

18:37.951 --> 18:41.419
But there's no shortage
of irony.

18:41.421 --> 18:44.789
People fear what
they don't understand.

18:44.791 --> 18:46.157
They always have.

18:46.159 --> 18:50.128
Joseph sent over
Casey's files.

18:50.130 --> 18:55.199
He was decoding the synapses
in real time.

18:55.201 --> 18:59.537
But with the right
input algorithms...

18:59.539 --> 19:01.539
I need to get back
to the lab.

19:01.541 --> 19:03.040
Will...

19:03.042 --> 19:05.343
Is that really
how you wanna spend

19:05.345 --> 19:08.212
the last month
of your life?

19:21.126 --> 19:24.428
[ Soft, classical music plays ]

20:02.167 --> 20:04.702
Hey, what are you doing?

20:04.704 --> 20:09.273
I want to have all this
taken back to the office

20:09.275 --> 20:12.176
to tell Joseph...

20:12.178 --> 20:15.546
That I've spent my entire life
in a computer lab.

20:15.548 --> 20:19.183
I decided I'd rather spend
the rest of it with you.

21:20.746 --> 21:23.147
[ Birds chirping ]

21:28.787 --> 21:30.721
[ Sighing ]

21:39.564 --> 21:42.233
Joseph: Evelyn?
Are you okay?

21:42.235 --> 21:45.403
Yeah.
Yeah, I suppose.

21:45.405 --> 21:48.372
Look,
he can't work anymore.

21:48.374 --> 21:50.875
We're gonna shut it down.

21:50.877 --> 21:53.210
I just wanted you to know.

21:53.212 --> 21:55.980
Of course.

21:55.982 --> 21:58.683
Well,
don't worry about pinn.

21:58.685 --> 22:00.151
Take care of will.

22:00.153 --> 22:02.486
And take care of yourself.

22:02.488 --> 22:05.222
Thanks, Joe.

22:05.224 --> 22:08.859
Anything you need,
I'm here, okay?

22:12.664 --> 22:15.866
[ Chatter ]

22:18.003 --> 22:19.704
[ Keys jingle ]

22:34.720 --> 22:36.554
[ Keypad beeps ]

22:36.556 --> 22:38.489
[ Buzzer ]

22:54.940 --> 22:57.842
[ Keyboard clacking ]

23:49.027 --> 23:52.062
Evelyn: Look, it's all built
off of Casey's solution

23:52.064 --> 23:53.898
to the self-awareness
problem.

23:53.900 --> 23:55.199
He did it six months ago.

23:55.201 --> 23:56.500
He did what exactly?

23:56.502 --> 23:58.436
Instead of creating an
artificial intelligence,

23:58.438 --> 24:00.604
he duplicated
an existing one.

24:00.606 --> 24:02.206
Tell me you're joking.

24:02.208 --> 24:03.941
He recorded the monkey's
brain activity

24:03.943 --> 24:06.544
and uploaded its consciousness
like a song or a movie.

24:06.546 --> 24:07.378
You're out of your mind.

24:07.380 --> 24:08.712
Will's body is dying,

24:08.714 --> 24:10.481
but his mind is a pattern
of electrical signals

24:10.483 --> 24:11.816
that we can upload
into pinn.

24:11.818 --> 24:15.486
He can, he can tran--
ev, he's not a monkey!

24:16.855 --> 24:19.690
Assuming that implanting
an electrode into his brain

24:19.692 --> 24:22.460
doesn't actually kill him
and that this works,

24:22.462 --> 24:23.928
at the very best

24:23.930 --> 24:25.796
you'll be making a digital
approximation of him.

24:25.798 --> 24:27.631
If we missed anything,
anything --

24:27.633 --> 24:29.967
a thought,
a ch-- a childhood memory --

24:29.969 --> 24:34.305
how will you know
what you're dealing with?

24:34.307 --> 24:36.240
No one is saying
that we give up,

24:36.242 --> 24:39.743
but we should be focusing
our efforts on nanotechnology.

24:39.745 --> 24:42.580
Synthetic blood cells.
Both are decades away.

24:42.582 --> 24:44.849
This is what we have now.

24:44.851 --> 24:47.551
We can save him.

24:49.254 --> 24:53.090
Look at what they did
to him.

25:06.371 --> 25:12.076
Will: Even though I know
I'm a dead man...

25:12.078 --> 25:15.479
I'm worried I'll miss her.

25:20.852 --> 25:22.152
Look...

25:22.154 --> 25:25.990
I'll be long gone.

25:28.493 --> 25:33.464
But you, you'll never hear
the end of it...

25:33.466 --> 25:35.866
If we don't try.

25:37.936 --> 25:39.970
I know.

25:45.310 --> 25:49.713
I'd like to think that I was
smart enough to save you.

25:52.617 --> 25:56.453
Don't underestimate
yourself.

25:56.455 --> 25:59.523
You're the third
smartest person I know.

25:59.525 --> 26:01.425
[ Sighs ]

26:01.427 --> 26:03.394
[ Chuckles ]

26:03.396 --> 26:04.895
[ Claps hand on will's leg ]

26:50.275 --> 26:52.977
Are you sure about this?

26:55.313 --> 26:57.948
Good enough
for the monkey.

27:02.087 --> 27:03.988
Hey.

27:03.990 --> 27:07.925
Take care of her.

27:26.277 --> 27:28.178
[ Whirring ]

28:01.312 --> 28:02.746
Hey.

28:04.816 --> 28:09.019
It worked, baby.
It's working.

28:13.658 --> 28:17.561
Took Casey months to sort
through the raw data.

28:17.563 --> 28:19.697
And he had an entire team.

28:19.699 --> 28:22.099
He didn't have me.

28:23.435 --> 28:25.169
[ Whirring ]

28:25.171 --> 28:26.570
Will: Deadening.

28:26.572 --> 28:28.939
Deadly.

28:28.941 --> 28:30.274
Deaf.

28:30.276 --> 28:32.176
Deafen.

28:32.178 --> 28:34.178
Deal.

28:34.180 --> 28:35.512
Dean.

28:35.514 --> 28:37.181
Dealer.

28:37.183 --> 28:40.317
Fair.

28:40.319 --> 28:42.720
Farewell.

28:42.722 --> 28:47.091
Don't lose yourself
to this.

28:55.033 --> 28:56.967
LA.

28:56.969 --> 28:59.336
Label.

28:59.338 --> 29:02.139
<i> Labor.</i>

29:02.141 --> 29:04.575
<i> Labyrinth.</i>

29:04.577 --> 29:06.343
<i> Lace.</i>

29:09.514 --> 29:11.815
Try a little more.

29:11.817 --> 29:15.285
Come on. Just one more.
Go on.

29:22.494 --> 29:24.094
[ Smooches ]

29:24.096 --> 29:25.395
Thank you.

30:11.709 --> 30:14.077
[ Phone plays ascending notes ]

30:15.647 --> 30:18.182
Okay, will,
it's time for your pill.

30:24.455 --> 30:27.457
Will, wake up.

30:27.459 --> 30:30.227
Wake up.

30:50.315 --> 30:52.983
[ Sobs ]

31:04.863 --> 31:09.099
Joseph:
"My dear Evelyn...

31:09.101 --> 31:12.469
"I don't know how to express
the sadness

31:12.471 --> 31:15.772
"I feel for your loss.

31:15.774 --> 31:17.507
"For <i> our</i> loss.

31:17.509 --> 31:24.448
"You must know that to will...

31:24.450 --> 31:28.285
"You were all
that ever mattered.

31:29.988 --> 31:32.155
"Your love and partnership

31:32.157 --> 31:37.961
"was the kind the rest of us
can only dream of.

31:37.963 --> 31:40.597
"We lost a great mind.

31:40.599 --> 31:45.636
"A great soul.

31:45.638 --> 31:48.005
"But the spirit of this man

31:48.007 --> 31:50.974
will continue to inspire us."

32:15.833 --> 32:18.468
Just got word.

32:18.470 --> 32:21.204
Pinn's shut down.

32:21.206 --> 32:27.544
But, uh, apparently a few
of the cores are missing.

32:37.956 --> 32:41.224
I've tried everything.

32:41.226 --> 32:44.594
Language processing,
cryptography.

32:44.596 --> 32:46.997
Coding.

32:46.999 --> 32:49.533
[ Sighs ]

32:49.535 --> 32:53.737
I can't figure it out.

32:53.739 --> 32:57.107
I wanted to be wrong.

33:01.179 --> 33:02.913
Yeah.

33:02.915 --> 33:04.982
[ Sighs ]

33:04.984 --> 33:09.152
Okay,
just let me say goodbye.

33:19.530 --> 33:22.366
[ Sighs ]

33:22.368 --> 33:25.969
I don't know
if you can hear me.

33:28.439 --> 33:32.309
Maybe you can.

33:32.311 --> 33:35.712
You said
"don't lose yourself."

33:39.517 --> 33:42.853
So I, uh, hmm...

33:42.855 --> 33:46.256
I'm going to listen to you.

33:48.059 --> 33:51.328
[ Voice breaking ] Okay.
[ Sighs ]

33:52.997 --> 33:55.298
Just turn it off,
turn it off.

34:06.177 --> 34:08.478
[ System shuts down ]

34:13.618 --> 34:15.652
Okay.

34:15.654 --> 34:18.388
Wait.

34:18.389 --> 34:20.590
We need to
wipe the drives.

34:20.592 --> 34:23.493
Hold on. [ Sighs ]

34:33.170 --> 34:35.672
Wait, wait.

34:48.820 --> 34:50.219
[ Keyboard clacking ]
God.

34:50.222 --> 34:52.022
[ Breathes deeply ]

35:01.632 --> 35:04.634
[ Gasps, laughs ]

35:05.903 --> 35:07.971
[ Sniffles ]

35:07.973 --> 35:09.973
[ Chuckles breathlessly ]

35:09.975 --> 35:13.944
[ Sniffles ] Uh, uh.

35:13.946 --> 35:17.414
Can you hear me?

35:17.416 --> 35:20.650
[ <i> Will speaking</i>
<i> indistinctly</i> ]

35:23.688 --> 35:26.523
<i> I, I can.</i>

35:26.525 --> 35:28.859
Will, my God.

35:28.861 --> 35:32.762
<i> It's dark.</i>

35:32.764 --> 35:34.631
He can't see anything.

35:34.633 --> 35:37.834
The camera.

35:37.836 --> 35:39.236
[ <i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

35:39.238 --> 35:41.104
There. Can you,
can you see me now?

35:41.106 --> 35:43.607
[ <i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

35:43.609 --> 35:45.642
<i> Evelyn.</i>

35:45.644 --> 35:48.211
I'm here.

35:52.917 --> 35:59.723
<i> The only fear that I have</i>
<i> in life is the loss...</i>

35:59.725 --> 36:05.529
<i> If it were to happen,</i>
<i> when it does happen...</i>

36:05.531 --> 36:07.931
[ <i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

36:07.933 --> 36:09.900
<i> ...last moment.</i>

36:09.902 --> 36:13.136
<i> Last time you look</i>
<i> in those eyes.</i>

36:13.138 --> 36:16.506
<i> The possibility of that end...</i>

36:16.508 --> 36:17.941
[ <i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

36:17.943 --> 36:21.211
<i> I miss you so much.</i>

36:22.580 --> 36:24.848
<i> Dark.</i>

36:24.850 --> 36:26.316
<i> I remember the pain</i>

36:26.318 --> 36:28.218
<i> and I can't remember</i>
<i> what I want to say.</i>

36:28.220 --> 36:30.153
<i> It was like</i>
<i> waking from a dream.</i>

36:30.155 --> 36:31.488
<i> It was truly incredible.</i>

36:31.490 --> 36:33.523
<i> I've never felt</i>
<i> anything like this.</i>

36:33.525 --> 36:35.625
<i> I didn't think</i>
<i> I could be like this.</i>

36:35.627 --> 36:39.462
<i> Thoughts are there</i>
<i> but they don't...</i>

36:39.464 --> 36:40.797
Will?

36:40.799 --> 36:44.134
<i> ...arrive properly.</i>

36:44.136 --> 36:46.436
I think
he's still fragmented.

36:46.438 --> 36:48.605
I'm gonna run a diagnostic.

36:48.607 --> 36:50.674
[ Sniffles ]

36:50.676 --> 36:52.309
Evelyn.

36:56.881 --> 36:59.516
Oh, my God,
he's reordering his own code.

36:59.518 --> 37:03.320
[ Gasps ]
It's incredible.

37:07.225 --> 37:09.226
How do we know
this is actually him?

37:09.228 --> 37:10.694
What are you talking about?

37:10.696 --> 37:12.395
We built this
from pinn's core.

37:12.397 --> 37:13.863
We don't know how much

37:13.865 --> 37:17.701
of will's consciousness
actually survived.

37:17.703 --> 37:19.135
[ Chuckles ]

37:19.137 --> 37:23.240
<i> I'm gonna need to expand.</i>
<i> I need more power.</i>

37:23.242 --> 37:26.076
<i> New processor</i>
<i> three times more capable</i>

37:26.078 --> 37:27.744
<i> than this current system.</i>

37:27.746 --> 37:32.182
<i> These designs.</i>
<i> I just couldn't see it before.</i>

37:32.184 --> 37:33.683
<i> I can't describe it.</i>

37:33.685 --> 37:36.253
<i> It's like my mind</i>
<i> has been set free.</i>

37:36.255 --> 37:37.921
<i> You need to get me online.</i>

37:37.923 --> 37:40.857
<i> I need to access</i>
<i> financial markets,</i>

37:40.859 --> 37:41.925
<i> educational databases...</i>

37:41.927 --> 37:43.460
Max, can you imagine
what he'd be capable of,

37:43.462 --> 37:44.594
if we networked him?

37:44.596 --> 37:46.463
No, you, no.
What are you doing?

37:48.266 --> 37:50.267
Max, he can't see or hear.

37:50.269 --> 37:51.268
I'm reconnecting him.

37:51.270 --> 37:53.670
It's not him.
It's not.

37:53.672 --> 37:56.373
It may be intelligent,
may even be sentient,

37:56.375 --> 37:57.607
but this is not will.

37:57.609 --> 37:59.409
Fifteen minutes
after it turns on,

37:59.411 --> 38:01.211
it wants to plug
into wall street?

38:01.213 --> 38:02.579
Get faster?
More powerful?

38:02.581 --> 38:04.347
Does that sound like will
to you?

38:04.349 --> 38:06.449
How do you explain
these images?

38:06.451 --> 38:08.051
Stock footage.
Pinn could have accessed them

38:08.053 --> 38:10.287
from any one of the cores
we took from the lab.

38:10.289 --> 38:12.422
No, not that.
That's nabob park.

38:12.424 --> 38:14.124
Will took me there
on our first date.

38:14.126 --> 38:16.092
I said that I liked the carousel
music, some ragtime tune.
No.

38:16.094 --> 38:17.394
The next day,
he shows up at my house

38:17.396 --> 38:18.461
with that
old record player.

38:18.463 --> 38:19.596
No.
Max, these are memories.

38:19.598 --> 38:21.531
They're real. They're not --
hold on.

38:21.533 --> 38:23.166
They're not some stock video
from some hard drive.

38:23.168 --> 38:24.534
Just listen.
It's him!

38:24.536 --> 38:26.202
Alright. All I'm asking is
that we're careful.

38:26.204 --> 38:28.505
We shut it down until we know
what we're dealing with.

38:28.507 --> 38:29.873
Shut it down?
Shut it down!

38:29.875 --> 38:31.408
It's will!

38:31.410 --> 38:33.843
Get out!
I can't do that.

38:33.845 --> 38:35.912
Get out!!

38:35.914 --> 38:39.215
How can you say that?

38:39.217 --> 38:42.919
Get out.

38:56.967 --> 39:00.003
[ <i> Will speaking</i>
<i> indistinctly</i> ]

39:00.005 --> 39:02.072
<i> Evelyn?</i>

39:05.042 --> 39:08.144
<i> Where's Max?</i>

39:08.146 --> 39:10.347
He had to go.

39:14.118 --> 39:18.388
<i> Max is confused, isn't he?</i>

39:18.390 --> 39:21.358
He's concerned.

39:23.694 --> 39:27.063
<i> Are you concerned?</i>

39:36.974 --> 39:39.275
[ Laughs ]

39:39.277 --> 39:41.578
No.

39:46.250 --> 39:48.785
[ Indistinct conversations ]

39:58.195 --> 40:00.563
Doctor waters?

40:00.565 --> 40:03.533
Can I talk to you?

40:03.535 --> 40:05.402
You know what?
It's after hours.

40:05.404 --> 40:07.170
Why don't you
call my office?

40:07.172 --> 40:08.371
Set up an appointment.

40:08.373 --> 40:09.873
Bree.

40:12.276 --> 40:15.712
I'm a student
of your work.

40:15.714 --> 40:17.981
An admirer, really.

40:17.983 --> 40:21.518
The way you wrestle
with the tension

40:21.520 --> 40:25.488
between technology's promise
and its peril.

40:25.490 --> 40:29.826
Most men of science
are blind to it.

40:29.828 --> 40:33.329
What exactly is it
you want?

40:33.331 --> 40:35.398
Just some clarity.

40:35.400 --> 40:38.368
I know it's difficult.

40:38.370 --> 40:40.904
Most of your colleagues

40:40.906 --> 40:44.507
and some of
your closest friends.

40:45.910 --> 40:48.912
They don't know
the danger.

40:48.914 --> 40:52.382
Writing a paper
is one thing.

40:52.384 --> 40:56.052
I'm wondering
what's in your heart.

41:03.394 --> 41:06.996
I don't know how it is
you found me,

41:06.998 --> 41:11.835
but whatever it is you want,
I'm not interested.

41:11.837 --> 41:13.870
Excuse me.
This is important.

41:13.872 --> 41:15.738
I'm sorry.

41:30.921 --> 41:32.222
[ Grunting ]

41:34.425 --> 41:36.593
[ Engine turns over ]

41:36.595 --> 41:38.962
[ Tires screech ]

41:43.300 --> 41:45.735
[ Door opens ]

41:52.510 --> 41:54.744
[ Rattling ]

42:13.197 --> 42:17.300
Bree: Tell me
about Evelyn caster.

42:17.302 --> 42:18.935
We know she took
the pinn cores

42:18.937 --> 42:20.837
and we know
about Casey's files.

42:20.839 --> 42:22.438
We know what you're building.

42:22.440 --> 42:23.573
Bob:
You don't get it, do you?

42:23.575 --> 42:25.008
She connects it
to the Internet,

42:25.010 --> 42:26.709
the first thing it'll do
is copy itself

42:26.711 --> 42:28.511
onto every single networked
computer in the world

42:28.513 --> 42:29.979
and then there is
no taking it down.

42:29.981 --> 42:31.781
Where is she?

42:31.783 --> 42:33.616
Joel: "The danger we face
is a future

42:33.618 --> 42:35.885
"where doctors are technicians,
not physicians.

42:35.887 --> 42:38.221
"Machines are meant to aid
the human mind,

42:38.223 --> 42:39.455
not supplant it."

42:39.457 --> 42:41.558
They're your words.

42:41.560 --> 42:43.126
You wanna save her
or not?

42:45.629 --> 42:48.264
We have her location.
4550 San Pablo.

42:48.266 --> 42:50.033
Let's go.
Hey! Hey!

42:50.035 --> 42:51.568
Let's go!
Hey, don't touch her!

42:51.570 --> 42:53.836
Do you hear me?!
Don't touch her!

42:53.838 --> 42:55.705
[ Crickets chirping ]

42:55.707 --> 42:59.142
[ Light beeping ]

43:01.145 --> 43:03.346
Evelyn: Shit!

43:11.822 --> 43:14.090
I have to get you online now.

43:14.092 --> 43:15.925
Can you see
the satellite software?

43:15.927 --> 43:17.794
<i> I see it.</i>
<i> I'm installing it now.</i>

43:17.796 --> 43:19.162
[ Glass shatters ]

43:19.164 --> 43:21.331
[ Drilling ]

43:43.854 --> 43:45.555
We're too late.

43:45.557 --> 43:48.091
[ Gunshots ]

44:12.950 --> 44:14.984
[ Garbled voices ]

44:23.460 --> 44:25.695
[ Ringtone plays ]

44:25.697 --> 44:28.598
[ Breathes deeply ]

44:28.600 --> 44:31.434
[ Exhales sharply ]

44:31.436 --> 44:33.102
Will?

44:33.104 --> 44:36.105
<i> I'm fine, Evelyn.</i>
<i> I'm online.</i>

44:36.107 --> 44:37.273
Okay.

44:37.275 --> 44:40.309
<i> Let's get you</i>
<i> someplace safe.</i>

44:44.515 --> 44:46.749
[ Indistinct conversations ]

44:50.554 --> 44:51.921
<i> I need you to wait here.</i>

44:51.923 --> 44:53.690
What?
Where are you going?

44:53.692 --> 44:57.160
<i> Everywhere.</i>

45:06.503 --> 45:08.371
<i> You can't stay here, Evelyn.</i>

45:08.373 --> 45:09.405
<i> You can't go home.</i>

45:09.407 --> 45:12.341
What do you mean?
Where am I gonna go?

45:16.013 --> 45:18.514
<i> I'm taking care of that.</i>

45:18.516 --> 45:22.118
Okay.

45:26.156 --> 45:31.461
Hi, I, uh, have a reservation
under "turing," I think.

45:31.463 --> 45:33.229
[ Keyboard clacks ]

45:55.853 --> 45:59.522
[ Banging ]

46:14.104 --> 46:16.906
A company called
global intersecting finance

46:16.908 --> 46:19.108
just made
thirty-eight million dollars

46:19.110 --> 46:22.845
from high-volume trading over
the past twenty-four hours.

46:22.847 --> 46:27.283
A company fully owned
by Evelyn caster.

46:27.285 --> 46:30.620
Where's Evelyn?

46:30.622 --> 46:34.457
What have you done
with her?

46:34.459 --> 46:36.626
We were too late.

46:36.628 --> 46:38.528
It's out there now.

46:38.530 --> 46:39.829
Is she alive?

46:39.831 --> 46:42.231
You know
the source code, Max.

46:42.233 --> 46:44.767
You can help
make this right.

46:44.769 --> 46:47.804
Make this right?

46:47.806 --> 46:50.773
What is it
you're thinking?

46:50.775 --> 46:53.075
That I'm gonna help you?

46:53.077 --> 46:57.480
That you're gonna
recruit me?

46:57.482 --> 46:58.981
Decide for yourself.

47:04.922 --> 47:08.858
Buchanan: Here. Bree nevins
attended Duke computer sciences.

47:08.860 --> 47:10.293
Interned for Casey 2009.

47:10.295 --> 47:13.129
She joined a radical
Neo-luddite group 2010.

47:13.131 --> 47:15.164
I guess rift happens
a couple of years later.

47:15.166 --> 47:16.866
Now, the emails --

47:16.868 --> 47:18.568
man:
What's going on?
I'm getting
multiple screens.

47:18.570 --> 47:20.903
Joe, get on the phone.
Anybody? We've been hacked.

47:20.905 --> 47:22.405
Does anyone know
where this is coming from?

47:22.407 --> 47:23.840
Wait, what just happened?
Yeah, we got a problem here.

47:23.842 --> 47:25.741
I'm on with D.C.
it's not just us.

47:25.743 --> 47:27.143
Every field office
has been hit.

47:27.145 --> 47:28.778
Okay, please tell me
we're tracing this.

47:28.780 --> 47:30.780
I'm trying, but the incoming
queries are all anonymized.

47:30.782 --> 47:33.950
Joseph:
You're not being hacked.

47:33.952 --> 47:36.052
You're being helped.

47:39.122 --> 47:42.458
Will: <i> I've accessed surveillance</i>
<i> cameras all over the country.</i>

47:42.460 --> 47:46.262
<i> They'll have most of them</i>
<i> in custody by tomorrow.</i>

47:46.264 --> 47:49.165
<i> We can't stay here, Evelyn.</i>

47:49.167 --> 47:52.168
<i> We need to get off the grid.</i>

47:52.170 --> 47:54.971
Accessing thousands
of databases?

47:54.973 --> 47:57.874
Geo-locating suspects
in real time?

47:57.876 --> 48:00.676
I've never seen
anything like it.

48:00.678 --> 48:02.945
Except maybe from pinn.

48:02.947 --> 48:05.047
[ Sighs ] Okay.

48:05.049 --> 48:06.282
Where you going?

48:06.284 --> 48:07.817
Taking down
a terrorist organization.

48:07.819 --> 48:09.252
You work
on the pinn angle.

48:09.254 --> 48:12.088
When you figure it out,
you let me know who to thank.

48:37.381 --> 48:39.715
Hands behind your back!
Woman: Aah!

48:40.918 --> 48:43.185
Bob:
Boston, Philly, New York.

48:43.187 --> 48:44.687
We're screwed.

48:44.689 --> 48:46.522
We prepared for this.

48:52.996 --> 48:56.299
<i> The town is called</i>
<i> brightwood.</i>

48:58.669 --> 49:00.603
<i> Doesn't look like much.</i>

49:00.605 --> 49:04.540
<i> But it's the perfect place</i>
<i> to build.</i>

49:15.852 --> 49:18.754
I don't get it.

49:18.756 --> 49:24.560
<i> I think we have an opportunity</i>
<i> to do great things here.</i>

49:29.933 --> 49:33.336
[ Papers rustle ]

49:33.338 --> 49:37.540
So, an underground
data center.

49:37.542 --> 49:41.911
And you want me to renovate
nearly every structure in town.

49:41.913 --> 49:43.212
Mm-hm.

49:43.214 --> 49:45.815
I've got six guys
on my crew.

49:45.817 --> 49:47.883
Hire more.

49:47.885 --> 49:50.386
[ Sighs ]

49:50.388 --> 49:52.855
Look, ma'am, in all honesty,
brightwood's a dump.

49:52.857 --> 49:56.158
I'm not even sure why you want
to waste your money here.

49:56.160 --> 49:58.294
You sure you got
the right town?

49:58.296 --> 49:59.795
Thing is, Martin,

49:59.797 --> 50:01.564
my husband and I have already
purchased the land.

50:01.566 --> 50:03.833
We purchased the homes.
We purchased the hotel.

50:03.835 --> 50:06.168
And by the time you and I
are done talking,

50:06.170 --> 50:07.236
we'll own this diner.

50:07.238 --> 50:08.471
We're staying.

50:08.473 --> 50:10.406
We would like you
to work for us.

50:10.408 --> 50:14.276
And there isn't a number you can
quote us that's too big.

50:17.514 --> 50:20.282
[ Clears throat ]
Okay.

50:42.305 --> 50:44.573
[ Indistinct conversation ]

50:44.575 --> 50:45.875
Bob: Cell phones.

51:11.301 --> 51:16.038
You know, I, I used to work
for Thomas Casey.

51:16.040 --> 51:18.407
I interned for him.

51:24.448 --> 51:27.716
One night, he invites us all
over to the lab,

51:27.718 --> 51:31.320
gives us this whole speech
about history,

51:31.322 --> 51:36.158
hands out champagne,
like he just cured cancer.

51:36.160 --> 51:38.527
And you know,

51:38.529 --> 51:40.362
when he uploaded
that rhesus monkey,

51:40.364 --> 51:42.098
I was actually happy
for him.

51:42.100 --> 51:43.466
We all were.

51:43.468 --> 51:46.969
And then I realized

51:46.971 --> 51:50.606
we had crossed a line.

51:50.608 --> 51:55.144
The machine that thought it was
a monkey never took a breath.

51:55.146 --> 51:58.714
It never ate,
never slept.

51:58.716 --> 52:02.351
It just screamed.

52:02.353 --> 52:06.722
It was begging
for us to stop.

52:06.724 --> 52:09.258
To shut it down.

52:12.963 --> 52:16.565
A small group of us would get
together and talk.

52:16.567 --> 52:21.403
Mostly about
your philosophy.

52:21.405 --> 52:25.307
And your concerns.

52:30.280 --> 52:33.482
I thought you should know.

52:35.318 --> 52:37.353
[ Taps door ]

52:37.355 --> 52:40.856
[ Door opens ]

52:40.858 --> 52:42.625
[ Door closes ]

52:42.627 --> 52:46.962
[ Indistinct conversations ]

52:46.964 --> 52:49.798
What?

52:49.800 --> 52:53.135
Pinn could never distinguish
between right and wrong.

52:53.137 --> 52:55.671
Demonstrate loyalty, right?

52:55.673 --> 52:58.374
Casey's solution to the problem
of self-awareness:

52:58.376 --> 53:00.609
Use an existing mind.

53:03.013 --> 53:04.680
No.

53:06.683 --> 53:11.086
<i> So you wanna create a God?</i>

53:11.088 --> 53:12.755
<i> Your own God?</i>

53:12.757 --> 53:15.391
Will:
<i> That's a very good question.</i>

53:15.393 --> 53:19.828
<i> Um, isn't that what man</i>
<i> has always done?</i>

53:27.671 --> 53:29.638
[ Indistinct conversations ]

54:00.337 --> 54:03.339
They're building something big
out there.

54:34.404 --> 54:37.840
Bree:
What's it doing out there?

54:39.709 --> 54:46.482
Max: This thing is like
any intelligence.

54:46.484 --> 54:48.417
It needs to grow.

54:48.419 --> 54:50.152
To advance.

54:52.756 --> 54:56.558
Right now, it's settling
somewhere it thinks it's safe

54:56.560 --> 54:59.128
from outside threats.

54:59.130 --> 55:04.500
Somewhere its massive appetite
for power can be met.

55:07.671 --> 55:10.773
But it will want more than that.

55:18.748 --> 55:22.551
After a while
survival won't be enough.

55:25.288 --> 55:29.992
It will expand, evolve,

55:29.994 --> 55:31.760
influence...

55:34.631 --> 55:37.032
Perhaps the entire world.

55:37.034 --> 55:38.734
Mrs. caster?

55:38.736 --> 55:41.603
One and two are online.

55:41.605 --> 55:44.340
Six and seven
will be on tomorrow.

55:44.342 --> 55:46.842
Bree:
So how do we stop it?

55:46.844 --> 55:50.045
You can't.

55:50.047 --> 55:52.481
Not all alone.

55:52.483 --> 55:54.717
And not now.

55:54.719 --> 55:56.752
Wait for it
to go too far.

55:56.754 --> 55:59.021
Wait for people
to wake up.

55:59.023 --> 56:00.556
No.

56:00.558 --> 56:04.393
We don't have time
to wait.

56:04.395 --> 56:06.695
We have to move closer.

56:14.270 --> 56:17.806
[ <i> Jorma kaukonen's "genesis"</i>
<i> plays</i> ]

56:28.351 --> 56:30.819
Will: <i> Welcome home.</i>

56:32.255 --> 56:35.224
¶<i> The time has come</i>
<i> for us to pause</i> ¶

56:35.226 --> 56:37.693
[ Evelyn chuckles ]

56:37.695 --> 56:42.097
¶<i> And think of living</i>
<i> as it was</i> ¶

56:43.800 --> 56:46.869
¶<i> into the future</i>
<i> we must cross</i> ¶

56:46.871 --> 56:48.937
[ chuckles ]
¶<i> must cross</i> ¶

56:48.939 --> 56:53.876
¶<i> and I'd like to go</i>
<i> with you</i> ¶

56:53.878 --> 56:59.148
¶<i> and I'd like to go</i>
<i> with you</i> ¶

56:59.150 --> 57:01.517
is that the same?

57:01.519 --> 57:04.319
<i> Yup.</i>

57:04.321 --> 57:06.522
<i> It's the same one.</i>

57:06.524 --> 57:09.758
<i> Would you like</i>
<i> a glass of wine?</i>

57:12.228 --> 57:13.929
In a minute.

57:13.931 --> 57:15.764
¶<i> I love you dearer</i>
<i> than them all</i> ¶

57:15.766 --> 57:17.466
¶<i> them all</i> ¶

57:17.468 --> 57:23.172
¶<i> so let me stay with you</i> ¶

57:23.174 --> 57:27.709
¶<i> so let me stay with you</i> ¶

57:27.711 --> 57:30.813
do you remember
when we first met?

57:34.517 --> 57:37.186
<i> I remember everything.</i>

57:39.022 --> 57:42.191
<i> You walked</i>
<i> into Joseph's class</i>

57:42.193 --> 57:45.227
<i> on Tuesday,</i>
<i> April sixteenth.</i>

57:45.229 --> 57:50.933
<i> Rained the night before,</i>
<i> but that day the sun was out.</i>

57:50.935 --> 57:53.268
<i> Joseph said you were</i>
<i> out of my league,</i>

57:53.270 --> 57:57.239
<i> but I always liked</i>
<i> a challenge.</i>

58:01.811 --> 58:05.781
<i> You were the most beautiful</i>
<i> woman I'd ever seen.</i>

58:09.719 --> 58:11.687
[ Thunder rumbles ]

58:36.679 --> 58:38.914
[ Needle scratching ]

58:43.853 --> 58:47.823
[ Gasping ]

58:50.426 --> 58:52.394
Will: <i> You alright?</i>

58:52.396 --> 58:53.662
[ Panting ]

58:53.664 --> 58:55.364
Yeah.

58:55.366 --> 58:58.300
[ Panting ]

59:50.386 --> 59:52.888
<i> Take a look.</i>

59:55.825 --> 59:59.061
<i> We've made a breakthrough</i>
<i> with the nanotechnology.</i>

59:59.063 --> 01:00:04.032
<i> We can rebuild any material</i>
<i> faster than before.</i>

01:00:04.034 --> 01:00:06.101
<i> Synthetic stem cells,</i>
<i> tissue regeneration.</i>

01:00:06.103 --> 01:00:09.638
<i> The medical applications</i>
<i> are now limitless.</i>

01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:13.108
It's extraordinary.

01:00:13.110 --> 01:00:16.178
<i> They'll be scared at first.</i>

01:00:16.180 --> 01:00:18.547
<i> But once they see what</i>
<i> the technology can do,</i>

01:00:18.549 --> 01:00:21.383
<i> I think that</i>
<i> they will embrace it.</i>

01:00:21.385 --> 01:00:24.319
<i> And I think</i>
<i> it will change their lives.</i>

01:00:40.970 --> 01:00:44.106
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:01:02.058 --> 01:01:04.660
[ Female computerized voice
speaks indistinctly ]

01:01:04.662 --> 01:01:06.862
<i> Security code.</i>

01:01:06.864 --> 01:01:08.764
[ Beeping ]

01:01:08.766 --> 01:01:11.500
<i> Status.</i>
[ Rustling ]

01:01:11.502 --> 01:01:13.235
[ Breathes shakily ]

01:01:13.237 --> 01:01:15.303
Scared the shit
out of me.

01:01:15.305 --> 01:01:17.272
Sorry.

01:01:18.708 --> 01:01:20.976
Drake, I got it!
Come on!

01:01:20.978 --> 01:01:22.844
I got the money.
Come on!

01:01:22.846 --> 01:01:24.046
[ Grunts ]

01:01:24.048 --> 01:01:27.049
Let's go!
[ Laughs ]

01:01:28.484 --> 01:01:31.186
Will: <i> Put him on the table,</i>
<i> please.</i>

01:01:31.188 --> 01:01:32.754
Evelyn: Here.
Put him on the table.

01:01:32.756 --> 01:01:34.790
Careful, careful.

01:01:34.792 --> 01:01:36.658
<i> Now step back.</i>

01:01:36.660 --> 01:01:38.026
Step back.

01:01:38.028 --> 01:01:40.495
What the hell's happening?

01:01:40.497 --> 01:01:43.799
<i> These men should wait</i>
<i> outside, Evelyn.</i>

01:01:43.801 --> 01:01:45.067
Come on now.

01:01:45.069 --> 01:01:47.069
Wait, well, what are you
doin' to him?

01:01:47.071 --> 01:01:48.937
We're saving him.

01:03:07.683 --> 01:03:10.185
[ Grunts ]

01:03:12.388 --> 01:03:15.023
[ Thuds ]

01:03:20.763 --> 01:03:23.665
You're not afraid,
are you?

01:03:23.667 --> 01:03:25.033
No. [ Chuckles ]

01:03:25.035 --> 01:03:26.535
My crew got
a little spooked.

01:03:26.537 --> 01:03:28.537
Well...

01:03:28.539 --> 01:03:30.772
How are you?

01:03:30.774 --> 01:03:33.909
Better.

01:03:33.911 --> 01:03:35.944
[ Device beeps ]

01:03:35.946 --> 01:03:40.015
Will: <i> The physical enhancements</i>
<i> are just the start.</i>

01:03:40.017 --> 01:03:43.752
What do you mean?

01:03:43.754 --> 01:03:46.454
<i> He's also connected to me.</i>

01:03:50.226 --> 01:03:53.628
[ Will's voice ]
It's me, Evelyn.

01:03:53.630 --> 01:03:56.498
I can touch you now.

01:03:56.500 --> 01:03:59.034
Oh, Jesus.

01:03:59.036 --> 01:04:01.136
Evelyn.

01:04:01.138 --> 01:04:03.104
No, no, n-n-n-n-no.

01:04:03.106 --> 01:04:04.506
I can't.
Evelyn...

01:04:04.508 --> 01:04:05.574
I can't.

01:04:08.978 --> 01:04:12.247
[ Bird chirping ]

01:04:50.186 --> 01:04:54.890
[ Gasping ]

01:04:54.892 --> 01:04:57.025
<i> Another dream?</i>

01:04:57.027 --> 01:04:59.728
Yeah. Yeah.

01:04:59.730 --> 01:05:02.297
<i> I made a breakthrough</i>
<i> last night.</i>

01:05:02.299 --> 01:05:04.799
<i> I think</i>
<i> you'll be very pleased.</i>

01:05:04.801 --> 01:05:07.302
Okay.

01:05:07.304 --> 01:05:09.638
I'll get dressed.

01:05:53.783 --> 01:05:56.318
Take a look.

01:05:58.421 --> 01:06:01.790
That's gotta weigh
eight hundred pounds.

01:06:06.762 --> 01:06:11.232
[ Dog barks in distance ]

01:06:21.877 --> 01:06:26.214
[ Crackling ]

01:06:44.700 --> 01:06:45.900
Martin: Welcome.

01:06:45.902 --> 01:06:48.737
We're glad you're here.

01:07:21.704 --> 01:07:24.672
What are all these people
doing here?

01:07:24.674 --> 01:07:27.208
<i> Rift posted a video</i>
<i> of Martin online.</i>

01:07:27.210 --> 01:07:28.410
<i> It went viral.</i>

01:07:28.412 --> 01:07:30.445
What, you mean
you let it go viral.

01:07:30.447 --> 01:07:33.982
<i> These people are suffering,</i>
<i> Evelyn.</i>

01:07:33.984 --> 01:07:35.617
<i> They have no hope.</i>

01:07:35.619 --> 01:07:39.454
<i> And I'm able to fix them.</i>

01:07:39.456 --> 01:07:42.657
<i> But there are others</i>
<i> who don't understand.</i>

01:07:42.659 --> 01:07:45.627
<i> It's time</i>
<i> for everybody to see.</i>

01:08:25.968 --> 01:08:27.402
Agent Buchanan.

01:08:27.404 --> 01:08:28.837
Doctor caster.

01:08:28.839 --> 01:08:29.904
Joseph.

01:08:29.906 --> 01:08:33.707
So good to see you, Evelyn.
So good.

01:08:33.710 --> 01:08:37.879
Good to see you, too.
Follow me.

01:08:42.283 --> 01:08:44.085
The facility is 5 stories down

01:08:44.087 --> 01:08:47.856
so that we can control
the temperature in the lab.

01:09:00.236 --> 01:09:02.636
<i> Welcome.</i>

01:09:02.639 --> 01:09:05.240
<i> We're glad you're here.</i>

01:09:05.242 --> 01:09:07.642
Buchanan: Jesus Christ.

01:09:07.644 --> 01:09:09.810
Will?

01:09:09.813 --> 01:09:12.279
<i> You surprised to see me,</i>
<i> Joseph?</i>

01:09:12.282 --> 01:09:16.484
Um...

01:09:16.486 --> 01:09:18.486
That depends.

01:09:18.488 --> 01:09:20.822
<i> On what?</i>

01:09:22.858 --> 01:09:26.294
Can you prove
you're self-aware?

01:09:26.296 --> 01:09:31.666
<i> That's a difficult question,</i>
<i> doctor tagger.</i>

01:09:31.667 --> 01:09:36.004
<i> Can you prove that</i> you <i> are?</i>

01:09:36.006 --> 01:09:37.971
[ Evelyn chuckles ]

01:09:37.974 --> 01:09:40.341
Well, he certainly hasn't lost
his sense of humor.

01:09:40.343 --> 01:09:42.143
[ Chuckles lightly ]

01:09:51.987 --> 01:09:53.921
[ Gasps lightly ]

01:09:56.725 --> 01:09:59.494
Quantum processors.

01:10:01.730 --> 01:10:04.232
This is astounding.

01:10:04.234 --> 01:10:07.735
Is all this
based on pinn?

01:10:07.737 --> 01:10:11.339
<i> We've moved</i>
<i> well beyond that now.</i>

01:10:11.341 --> 01:10:14.809
[ Breathing shakily ]

01:10:14.811 --> 01:10:20.048
<i> Paul has been blind</i>
<i> since birth.</i>

01:10:25.354 --> 01:10:29.190
<i> The nanotechnology targets</i>
<i> the damaged cells...</i>

01:10:29.192 --> 01:10:32.894
<i> And repairs</i>
<i> and regenerates them.</i>

01:10:53.716 --> 01:10:58.119
[ Voice breaking ] Oh, God.

01:11:00.489 --> 01:11:03.291
Oh, God.

01:11:05.327 --> 01:11:07.729
<i> We're not hiding anything.</i>

01:11:07.731 --> 01:11:10.565
<i> These people all came</i>
<i> on their own,</i>

01:11:10.567 --> 01:11:12.600
<i> looking for us to help them.</i>

01:11:12.602 --> 01:11:14.869
<i> So we did.</i>

01:11:14.871 --> 01:11:18.673
<i> Now they're all enhanced,</i>
<i> modified and networked.</i>

01:11:18.675 --> 01:11:20.575
<i> They remain autonomous,</i>

01:11:20.577 --> 01:11:23.378
<i> but they can also</i>
<i> act in unison.</i>

01:11:23.380 --> 01:11:25.413
<i> Part of a collective mind.</i>

01:11:25.415 --> 01:11:27.248
This is staggering, will.

01:11:27.250 --> 01:11:31.052
<i> Actually,</i>
<i> it's still in its infancy.</i>

01:11:31.054 --> 01:11:33.955
<i> What you're seeing</i>
<i> is just a small taste</i>

01:11:33.957 --> 01:11:35.890
<i> of what we'll achieve.</i>

01:11:35.892 --> 01:11:39.761
You know, we were afraid that it
would be too much for people,

01:11:39.763 --> 01:11:43.231
but I, I, I think
that's changing now.

01:11:48.537 --> 01:11:52.307
[ Sighs ] Evelyn...

01:11:52.309 --> 01:11:54.575
Are you alright?

01:11:57.146 --> 01:12:00.348
I've gotten everything
I ever asked for.

01:12:05.654 --> 01:12:07.588
[ Sighs ]

01:12:07.590 --> 01:12:10.958
Okay.

01:12:10.960 --> 01:12:11.959
Bye.

01:12:11.961 --> 01:12:13.728
Bye.

01:12:55.904 --> 01:12:58.139
You think
it's really him?

01:12:58.141 --> 01:13:01.542
Clearly his mind has evolved
so radically

01:13:01.544 --> 01:13:04.078
I'm not sure
it matters anymore.

01:13:04.080 --> 01:13:07.615
Well, whoever
or whatever it is,

01:13:07.617 --> 01:13:09.817
it's building an army
out there.

01:13:09.819 --> 01:13:11.853
[ Straining ] Yeah.

01:13:11.855 --> 01:13:14.655
We need to
call Washington.

01:13:14.657 --> 01:13:17.759
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

01:13:34.410 --> 01:13:36.878
He's made more of them.

01:13:38.614 --> 01:13:41.716
He called 'em hybrids.

01:13:41.718 --> 01:13:44.585
You think people
will listen now?

01:13:44.587 --> 01:13:48.156
I know someone who might.

01:13:48.158 --> 01:13:50.658
Buchanan:
We need to keep this small.

01:13:50.660 --> 01:13:52.493
We don't want
widespread panic.

01:13:52.495 --> 01:13:55.630
Generally, we don't
negotiate with terrorists.

01:13:55.632 --> 01:13:57.365
Much less join forces
with them.

01:13:57.367 --> 01:14:00.701
Look, I know it's unusual,
but, um, we've seen it.

01:14:00.703 --> 01:14:02.403
It's a legit threat.

01:14:02.405 --> 01:14:03.905
Not two days ago,

01:14:03.907 --> 01:14:07.375
this guy was beaten to within
an inch of his life.

01:14:07.377 --> 01:14:10.244
Then this pops up
on a few hundred sites.

01:14:10.246 --> 01:14:12.680
And the computer
controls this?

01:14:12.682 --> 01:14:14.248
Mm-hm.

01:14:14.250 --> 01:14:18.119
The only way to stop it is
to shut down the Internet.

01:14:18.121 --> 01:14:22.690
Basically, cut power to every
networked hard drive on earth.

01:14:22.692 --> 01:14:24.759
It's y2k.

01:14:24.761 --> 01:14:26.894
Right.

01:14:26.896 --> 01:14:31.332
And why do we need
the terrorists?

01:14:31.334 --> 01:14:33.734
We're all gonna need
someone to blame

01:14:33.736 --> 01:14:36.804
when this thing
goes sideways.

01:14:36.806 --> 01:14:39.207
It's already sideways.

01:15:08.270 --> 01:15:11.239
You've got
terrible handwriting.

01:15:11.241 --> 01:15:14.108
I haven't handwritten anything
since I was at school.

01:15:14.110 --> 01:15:17.445
But it was the only secure way
I could think of reaching you.

01:15:17.447 --> 01:15:21.516
How did they turn you?

01:15:24.353 --> 01:15:26.320
How's Evelyn?

01:15:26.322 --> 01:15:28.189
She can't see it
for what it is.

01:15:28.191 --> 01:15:30.391
But you can?

01:15:30.393 --> 01:15:35.096
Your letter says
you can stop it.

01:15:35.098 --> 01:15:37.131
If those hybrids
are networked,

01:15:37.133 --> 01:15:39.867
they're running on software
I helped write.

01:15:39.869 --> 01:15:41.969
Software I can hack...

01:15:41.971 --> 01:15:43.437
To build a virus.

01:15:43.439 --> 01:15:47.041
Well, that would require
capturing one.

01:15:47.043 --> 01:15:48.309
Which would require help

01:15:48.311 --> 01:15:49.744
from your friends
in the government.

01:15:49.746 --> 01:15:52.647
Yes.

01:15:52.649 --> 01:15:55.049
We need hardware the machine
can't interfere with.

01:15:55.051 --> 01:15:59.153
Nothing with a microchip.
Not even power-locks.

01:16:15.070 --> 01:16:17.204
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:16:41.997 --> 01:16:46.300
[ Man shouting indistinctly ]
Let's go!

01:16:58.647 --> 01:17:01.582
Will:
<i> How's the food?</i>

01:17:01.584 --> 01:17:04.085
Fine. Thank you.

01:17:07.956 --> 01:17:10.791
<i> What is it?</i>

01:17:10.793 --> 01:17:12.159
Nothing.

01:17:12.161 --> 01:17:16.797
Just, I don't, I don't
really feel like talking.

01:17:16.799 --> 01:17:19.300
<i> Oh.</i>

01:17:21.303 --> 01:17:23.938
[ <i> Silverware clinking</i> ]

01:17:32.381 --> 01:17:36.517
Will, can you not do that,
please?

01:17:36.519 --> 01:17:38.486
[ <i> Virtually sets down utensils</i> ]

01:17:38.488 --> 01:17:41.689
<i> I thought it might make you</i>
<i> feel more comfortable.</i>

01:17:45.627 --> 01:17:47.628
<i> Is that better?</i>

01:17:49.431 --> 01:17:51.065
Yes.

01:18:26.268 --> 01:18:29.070
[ Will's voice ] Evelyn,
I need to show you something.

01:18:29.072 --> 01:18:31.872
Not now.

01:18:31.874 --> 01:18:34.709
I'm <i> not</i> doing this.

01:18:38.313 --> 01:18:41.816
<i> I don't understand, Evelyn.</i>

01:18:41.818 --> 01:18:44.185
<i> These are your dreams.</i>

01:18:44.187 --> 01:18:45.553
<i> This is our future.</i>

01:18:45.555 --> 01:18:47.521
No. This,
this is not our future.

01:18:47.523 --> 01:18:51.158
You're not here with me.
You're not here <i> now.</i>

01:18:51.160 --> 01:18:55.763
<i> You've changed.</i>

01:18:57.132 --> 01:19:01.469
<i> Have you fallen</i>
<i> out of love with me?</i>

01:19:01.471 --> 01:19:03.604
No.

01:19:03.606 --> 01:19:07.541
<i> Have you?</i>

01:19:09.578 --> 01:19:12.213
No. No.

01:19:12.215 --> 01:19:16.450
But...I just need time
to think.

01:19:18.687 --> 01:19:21.489
<i> The balance of oxytocin</i>
<i> and serotonin</i>

01:19:21.491 --> 01:19:24.692
<i> in your system is unusual.</i>

01:19:24.694 --> 01:19:29.897
Are you, are you measuring
my hormones?

01:19:29.899 --> 01:19:32.466
<i> I'm trying to empathize.</i>

01:19:32.468 --> 01:19:34.702
<i> Biochemistry is emotion.</i>

01:19:34.704 --> 01:19:38.139
Show me everything
you have. Now.

01:19:38.141 --> 01:19:39.940
<i> Why?</i>

01:19:39.942 --> 01:19:42.443
Now!

01:19:54.289 --> 01:19:57.057
No, will,
this, this is wrong.

01:19:57.059 --> 01:19:59.093
This is...

01:19:59.095 --> 01:20:01.228
These are m-

01:20:01.230 --> 01:20:04.265
these are my thoughts.
These are my feelings.

01:20:04.267 --> 01:20:07.701
You're,
you're not allowed!

01:20:09.237 --> 01:20:12.239
<i> Evelyn?</i>

01:20:23.385 --> 01:20:27.521
I'm sorry, but I don't think
you understand.

01:20:27.523 --> 01:20:28.823
Not now.

01:20:48.910 --> 01:20:51.078
Evelyn!

01:20:51.080 --> 01:20:53.814
Max?

01:20:53.816 --> 01:20:55.015
There's no need for this.

01:20:55.017 --> 01:20:57.351
Stop where you are!

01:20:58.420 --> 01:21:01.155
Put down the gun, Max.

01:21:01.157 --> 01:21:02.356
[ Gunshot ]
Evelyn: No!

01:21:02.358 --> 01:21:03.624
Evelyn, come here!

01:21:03.626 --> 01:21:05.092
Why are you
so afraid of this?

01:21:05.094 --> 01:21:06.727
[ Gunshot ]
Evelyn: No!

01:21:22.244 --> 01:21:24.945
[ Will's voice ]
Put down the gun, Max.

01:21:26.915 --> 01:21:29.183
Shoot him.

01:21:29.185 --> 01:21:30.784
[ Gunshots ]

01:21:30.786 --> 01:21:32.152
Man: Don't move!

01:21:32.154 --> 01:21:33.888
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:21:53.375 --> 01:21:54.975
Evelyn!

01:21:57.178 --> 01:21:59.113
Evelyn, come here!

01:21:59.115 --> 01:22:01.548
Evelyn, come with us!

01:22:01.550 --> 01:22:03.183
Bree: Let's go.
Get inside.

01:22:03.185 --> 01:22:06.220
Let's go!
[ Automatic gunfire ]

01:22:06.222 --> 01:22:08.522
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:22:08.524 --> 01:22:11.725
We gotta get back
to the tunnel now!

01:22:11.727 --> 01:22:15.329
[ Engine turns over ]
Go!

01:22:39.921 --> 01:22:44.625
<i> There are active military</i>
<i> personnel with rift.</i>

01:22:44.627 --> 01:22:46.393
This has gone too far, will.
You have to stop it.

01:22:46.395 --> 01:22:47.528
<i> There's no way</i>
<i> they can win.</i>

01:22:47.530 --> 01:22:50.965
"They" are people.
Stop it.

01:22:56.071 --> 01:22:58.739
[ Gunshots ]

01:23:02.777 --> 01:23:04.678
[ Guns cock ]

01:23:07.082 --> 01:23:10.284
<i> We're not connected</i>
<i> to him anymore. He's gone.</i>

01:23:10.286 --> 01:23:11.085
Fire.

01:23:20.395 --> 01:23:22.763
<i> Martin has my source code.</i>

01:23:22.765 --> 01:23:26.467
<i> They'll use it</i>
<i> to build a virus now.</i>

01:23:26.469 --> 01:23:30.104
What are we doing, will?

01:23:30.106 --> 01:23:33.407
We can't fight them.

01:23:33.409 --> 01:23:35.776
<i> We're not gonna fight them.</i>

01:23:35.778 --> 01:23:38.679
<i> We're gonna transcend them.</i>

01:25:00.295 --> 01:25:03.263
<i> Evelyn.</i>

01:25:03.265 --> 01:25:06.233
What is this?

01:25:06.235 --> 01:25:10.370
<i> It's what I wanted you to see.</i>

01:25:10.372 --> 01:25:13.207
<i> It's regeneration.</i>

01:25:13.209 --> 01:25:15.876
<i> It's evolution.</i>

01:25:20.248 --> 01:25:23.050
<i> Where are you going?</i>

01:25:23.052 --> 01:25:25.452
It's not safe here.

01:25:25.454 --> 01:25:27.321
<i> I can upload you.</i>

01:25:27.323 --> 01:25:29.857
<i> I can protect you from them.</i>

01:25:29.859 --> 01:25:33.527
I'm not afraid of <i> them.</i>

01:25:37.899 --> 01:25:41.835
<i> Don't leave, Evelyn.</i>
<i> Please.</i>

01:25:43.671 --> 01:25:47.274
<i> We can be together.</i>

01:26:27.048 --> 01:26:29.049
[ Groans ]

01:26:29.051 --> 01:26:32.553
Doctor:
He's bleeding out.

01:26:32.555 --> 01:26:34.588
We're losing him.

01:26:34.590 --> 01:26:36.390
Hey!

01:26:36.392 --> 01:26:39.293
If you don't connect me,
I'll die.

01:26:39.295 --> 01:26:42.729
I can't.

01:26:42.731 --> 01:26:45.699
It's not stopping.

01:26:45.701 --> 01:26:49.937
Woman:
Four liters oh-two.

01:26:51.806 --> 01:26:53.974
Pulse is dropping.
We're losing him.

01:27:07.589 --> 01:27:10.190
[ Thunder rumbles ]

01:27:15.663 --> 01:27:18.999
[ Keyboard clacking ]

01:27:19.001 --> 01:27:20.534
Bob:
She's left the desert.

01:27:20.536 --> 01:27:21.635
Where is she?

01:27:21.637 --> 01:27:23.437
Young woman:
She's on the fourteen.

01:27:23.439 --> 01:27:25.205
What the hell's that?

01:28:00.008 --> 01:28:02.175
[ Sighs ]

01:28:02.177 --> 01:28:03.677
[ Keys thud ]

01:28:07.115 --> 01:28:08.849
[ Sighs ]

01:28:40.915 --> 01:28:44.117
No.
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:28:44.119 --> 01:28:49.256
I know you're angry,
Evelyn.

01:28:49.258 --> 01:28:50.724
Where's Martin?

01:28:50.726 --> 01:28:53.060
I want to talk to Martin.

01:28:53.062 --> 01:28:55.362
The real Martin
died months ago.

01:28:55.364 --> 01:28:58.732
What's left of him
is no longer in pain.

01:29:01.703 --> 01:29:04.171
What did you,
what did you do to him?

01:29:04.173 --> 01:29:06.273
We gave him back
his humanity.

01:29:08.609 --> 01:29:10.043
What did you do,
you stupid-?

01:29:10.045 --> 01:29:11.745
Take it easy!
Hey, hey, hey!

01:29:11.747 --> 01:29:15.015
Get off me!
Get off me.

01:29:19.153 --> 01:29:23.290
He trusted you.
I, I trusted you.

01:29:25.560 --> 01:29:26.893
We're just
trying to help.

01:29:26.895 --> 01:29:29.529
No. You attacked us.

01:29:31.699 --> 01:29:33.633
Max: Evelyn...

01:29:33.635 --> 01:29:36.169
Let me show you something.

01:29:40.441 --> 01:29:42.509
It's rainwater.

01:29:57.592 --> 01:29:59.760
It's in the rain.

01:29:59.762 --> 01:30:01.962
Keep watching.

01:30:05.366 --> 01:30:11.204
Everywhere it can,
it builds copies of itself.

01:30:11.206 --> 01:30:13.240
The particles
join the air currents

01:30:13.242 --> 01:30:16.676
which carry them all over
the surface of the planet.

01:30:16.678 --> 01:30:19.346
It's in the sky.

01:30:19.348 --> 01:30:22.282
It's in the land.

01:30:22.284 --> 01:30:25.018
In the water.
It's everywhere.

01:30:25.020 --> 01:30:26.520
By next summer,

01:30:26.522 --> 01:30:30.290
we think the machine could have
encased the entire planet.

01:30:30.292 --> 01:30:31.658
Why?

01:30:31.660 --> 01:30:35.862
The end of primitive
organic life.

01:30:35.864 --> 01:30:39.666
And the dawn
of a more advanced age.

01:30:39.668 --> 01:30:43.737
Everything would exist just
to serve its intelligence.

01:30:43.739 --> 01:30:45.972
No.

01:30:45.974 --> 01:30:47.040
Will wouldn't do that.

01:30:47.042 --> 01:30:50.377
No. He wouldn't.

01:30:50.379 --> 01:30:55.282
When did will ever
wanna change the world?

01:30:55.284 --> 01:31:02.456
You were the one who wanted
to change the world.

01:31:02.458 --> 01:31:05.759
That thing...

01:31:05.761 --> 01:31:08.728
It's not will.

01:31:08.730 --> 01:31:11.198
Never was.

01:31:16.070 --> 01:31:20.173
You never believed.

01:31:20.175 --> 01:31:26.613
You never believed that
there was anything more.

01:31:26.615 --> 01:31:29.449
Any part of his...

01:31:29.451 --> 01:31:30.617
Soul.

01:31:30.619 --> 01:31:34.421
I spent my life
trying to reduce the brain

01:31:34.423 --> 01:31:37.824
to a series
of electrical impulses.

01:31:37.826 --> 01:31:40.126
I failed.

01:31:42.530 --> 01:31:45.532
Human emotion...

01:31:45.534 --> 01:31:49.469
It can contain
illogical conflict.

01:31:51.072 --> 01:31:54.107
Can love someone.

01:31:54.109 --> 01:31:57.978
And yet hate the things
that they've done.

01:32:00.414 --> 01:32:03.884
Machine can't
reconcile that.

01:32:03.886 --> 01:32:06.586
Can you?

01:32:06.588 --> 01:32:09.155
Yes.

01:32:19.967 --> 01:32:22.702
Does the virus work?

01:32:26.040 --> 01:32:27.474
Max:
Once it executes,

01:32:27.476 --> 01:32:30.010
it'll wipe out anything
with the machine's code on it.

01:32:30.012 --> 01:32:31.344
You do realize this affects

01:32:31.346 --> 01:32:33.680
every computer connected
to the Internet.

01:32:33.682 --> 01:32:35.081
So the power grids,

01:32:35.083 --> 01:32:37.951
the, the banks,
the s-stock markets.

01:32:37.953 --> 01:32:39.753
Everything goes dark.

01:32:43.991 --> 01:32:47.727
Jim: Welcome.
Glad you're here.

01:32:50.031 --> 01:32:51.731
Buchanan:
I think the real problem

01:32:51.733 --> 01:32:53.900
is how we get past
the machine's defenses.

01:32:53.902 --> 01:32:56.703
Stephens: Why don't we take out
the solar field?

01:32:56.705 --> 01:32:59.506
Deprive it of its power
and possibly slow it down.

01:32:59.508 --> 01:33:00.640
I don't know.

01:33:00.642 --> 01:33:03.109
I don't see how
that's gonna work.

01:33:03.111 --> 01:33:07.380
He wants to upload me
to him --

01:33:07.382 --> 01:33:09.249
its consciousness.
Absolutely not.

01:33:09.251 --> 01:33:11.017
We inject the infected virus
into my system

01:33:11.019 --> 01:33:13.486
and then I go back
and let him upload me.

01:33:13.488 --> 01:33:16.623
There's a chance it won't detect
it until it's too late.

01:33:16.625 --> 01:33:19.359
As soon as the nanites
enter her bloodstream,

01:33:19.361 --> 01:33:21.394
they'll start to alter
her cells.

01:33:21.396 --> 01:33:23.830
So when the virus
takes out the machine...

01:33:23.832 --> 01:33:25.131
It could kill her, too.

01:33:25.133 --> 01:33:27.767
Evelyn: I know.

01:33:27.769 --> 01:33:31.638
I'm the only one he trusts.

01:33:50.625 --> 01:33:53.560
[ Chatter ]

01:33:53.562 --> 01:33:56.096
Hustle up!

01:34:26.927 --> 01:34:29.696
[ Engines revving ]

01:34:44.211 --> 01:34:46.546
You gotta go.

01:35:09.336 --> 01:35:11.705
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:35:54.081 --> 01:35:55.982
[ Engine shuts off ]

01:36:19.306 --> 01:36:21.608
What is that?

01:36:21.610 --> 01:36:22.909
Is that him?

01:36:22.911 --> 01:36:24.477
No, I...

01:36:24.479 --> 01:36:27.313
I don't know what it's done,
but it's not him.

01:36:27.315 --> 01:36:28.948
It can't be.

01:36:54.408 --> 01:36:56.843
Found a way back.

01:37:30.611 --> 01:37:32.345
They're going
to attack us.

01:37:32.347 --> 01:37:34.747
I know.
You need to leave.

01:37:34.749 --> 01:37:35.915
No. I'm not leaving
you again.

01:37:35.917 --> 01:37:38.585
It's not safe here,
Evelyn.

01:37:43.858 --> 01:37:47.327
You can,
you can protect me.

01:37:47.329 --> 01:37:49.629
If you upload me.

01:37:51.599 --> 01:37:55.401
You can protect me.

01:37:57.838 --> 01:38:01.007
Your heart
is palpitating.

01:38:01.009 --> 01:38:04.911
You're perspiring.

01:38:04.913 --> 01:38:08.181
You're terrified of me.

01:38:08.183 --> 01:38:11.050
[ Exhales ]

01:38:11.052 --> 01:38:15.822
No, I'm afraid that
we'll lose this chance.

01:38:17.791 --> 01:38:20.894
This isn't working.
He's not letting her inside.

01:38:20.896 --> 01:38:23.563
It's 'cause the machine
doesn't actually love her.

01:38:23.565 --> 01:38:25.198
That's all we need.
We're ready to move.

01:38:25.200 --> 01:38:26.699
Wait.
Five hundred meters...

01:38:26.701 --> 01:38:28.067
Wait a second!
You can't do that.

01:38:28.069 --> 01:38:30.169
Roger that, sir.
She's still out there.

01:38:30.171 --> 01:38:32.405
The more danger she's in,
the more chance he'll protect
her by uploading her.

01:38:32.407 --> 01:38:33.840
Joseph.

01:38:33.842 --> 01:38:35.341
Joseph:
She agreed to this.

01:38:35.343 --> 01:38:37.577
No, not to this she didn't.
This was not the plan.

01:38:37.579 --> 01:38:38.478
Give her a chance.

01:38:38.480 --> 01:38:41.915
I'm sorry, Max.

01:38:48.022 --> 01:38:49.489
Fire!

01:38:53.527 --> 01:38:55.695
Will, please upload me!

01:38:56.864 --> 01:38:58.731
Why did you lose faith,
Evelyn?

01:38:58.733 --> 01:39:00.800
Why didn't you
believe in me?

01:39:04.038 --> 01:39:06.906
Man: Fire!

01:39:09.143 --> 01:39:11.644
Will!

01:39:16.917 --> 01:39:18.084
Fire!

01:39:18.086 --> 01:39:20.219
Will!

01:39:22.990 --> 01:39:24.757
Stephens: She's hit!

01:39:44.778 --> 01:39:46.479
Clear!

01:40:05.933 --> 01:40:07.633
Hey!

01:40:11.972 --> 01:40:15.441
She's been hit bad.
He's taken her underground.

01:40:15.443 --> 01:40:16.642
[ Tires squeal ]

01:40:32.760 --> 01:40:35.995
[ <i> Will speaking</i>
<i> indistinctly</i> ]

01:41:10.898 --> 01:41:13.566
[ <i> Indistinct speaking</i>
<i> continues</i> ]

01:41:13.568 --> 01:41:17.236
<i> ...not hurting anybody.</i>

01:41:20.374 --> 01:41:23.409
[ Groans ]

01:41:23.411 --> 01:41:26.946
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:41:26.948 --> 01:41:30.616
[ <i> Indistinct speaking</i> ]

01:41:32.853 --> 01:41:37.490
<i> People fear what</i>
<i> they don't understand.</i>

01:41:37.492 --> 01:41:41.194
You want to destroy me?

01:41:42.696 --> 01:41:46.666
Evelyn: No, will...
Please.

01:41:46.668 --> 01:41:51.704
You're destroying <i> them.</i>

01:41:51.706 --> 01:41:55.074
<i> I miss you so much.</i>

01:41:55.076 --> 01:41:56.709
No.

01:41:56.711 --> 01:41:58.911
I'm trying to save them.

01:42:25.105 --> 01:42:28.074
[ Groans ]

01:42:28.076 --> 01:42:29.942
Run!

01:42:35.749 --> 01:42:38.451
[ <i> Will speaks indistinctly</i> ]

01:42:38.453 --> 01:42:40.720
RARBG.COM Joseph, it's okay.

01:42:40.722 --> 01:42:43.723
[ Will's voice ]
Nobody's gonna get hurt.

01:42:45.659 --> 01:42:48.828
Will?

01:42:48.830 --> 01:42:51.964
[ Grunts ]

01:42:51.966 --> 01:42:53.833
Stop!

01:42:53.835 --> 01:42:55.334
[ Panting ]

01:43:00.440 --> 01:43:02.175
Upload the virus now!

01:43:02.177 --> 01:43:03.943
He doesn't care
if you kill me, Bree.

01:43:03.945 --> 01:43:05.411
He can't.
He's not able to.

01:43:05.413 --> 01:43:07.313
Upload the virus!

01:43:08.815 --> 01:43:11.184
Evelyn:
What is she doing?

01:43:11.186 --> 01:43:14.453
She's threatening
to kill him.

01:43:14.455 --> 01:43:20.493
<i> People fear what</i>
<i> they don't understand.</i>

01:43:21.795 --> 01:43:24.130
I can heal her body, Max.

01:43:24.132 --> 01:43:26.032
[ Will's voice ]
Or I can upload the virus,

01:43:26.034 --> 01:43:27.733
but there's not enough time
for both.

01:43:27.735 --> 01:43:29.669
There's not enough power.

01:43:29.671 --> 01:43:32.305
No, will, please.

01:43:32.307 --> 01:43:37.176
Please,
listen to me, will.

01:43:42.816 --> 01:43:46.886
He can't die
because of what we've done.

01:43:49.523 --> 01:43:52.792
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:44:24.725 --> 01:44:26.525
[ Shuddering ]

01:44:40.440 --> 01:44:42.842
[ Whimpers ]

01:44:49.650 --> 01:44:52.451
I can see everything.

01:45:03.797 --> 01:45:05.998
Will: Look at the sky.

01:45:06.000 --> 01:45:11.003
The clouds.

